Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 12:30:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] timestamp: reject odd single-channel timestamp cadence

For one complex I/Q channel the 64-bit DMA bus carries two complex
samples per packed word. The FPGA timestamp block expects
timestamp_every in packed-word units, so odd complex-sample cadences
cannot be represented without changing host buffer sizing as well.
---
 PlutoSDR_TimestampEvery.hpp | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/PlutoSDR_TimestampEvery.hpp b/PlutoSDR_TimestampEvery.hpp
--- a/PlutoSDR_TimestampEvery.hpp
+++ b/PlutoSDR_TimestampEvery.hpp
@@ -21,6 +21,11 @@ namespace SoapyPlutoSDR_TimestampEvery
         // in each 64-bit value. We do not need to divide the requested timestamp value.
         if (channel_count == 2)
         {
+            if ((value & 1U) != 0U)
+            {
+                SoapySDR_logf(SOAPY_SDR_ERROR, "timestamp_every must be even for one complex channel");
+                throw std::runtime_error("timestamp_every must be even for one complex channel");
+            }
             value /= 2;
         }
 
